<doc id="86080" wikidata="Q728572" url="?curid=86080" title="Amergin">
<text>Amergin, also spelled Amorgen, Amairgin, Aimhirghin, Amorghain, may refer to:

* Amergin Glúingel, poet and druid of the Irish Mythological Cycle
* Amergin mac Eccit, poet and hero of the Irish Ulster Cycle
* Amergin of Maigh Seóla ( 550), father of Finbarr of Cork, Ireland
* Amergin, a crater on Europa
* &quot;Amergin: An Enigma of the Forest&quot;, 1978 novel by Sven Berlin</text><links>
